      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In the meantime, there are some things you can try to help calm your symptoms. Deep breathing exercises, such as inhaling through your nose and exhaling slowly through your mouth, may help ease anxiety and nausea. You can also try progressive muscle relaxation, where you tense and then relax different muscle groups in your body. A warm bath or a calming tea, like chamomile, might also help soothe your symptoms. Additionally, try to establish a relaxing bedtime routine to signal to your brain that it's time to wind down and sleep.",
      "source": "target",
